description:
I challenged myself to make oatscaldo using only dried goods that travel well and are suitable for my 6-day quarantine at a government-approved hotel in Manila.

OATSCALDO 
INGREDIENTS:
1 liters water
1 cup oats
1-2 tablespoons fried garlic
2 tablespoons dried chopped onions
1 teaspoon dried ginger
few pinches of white pepper
1 tablespoon mushroom powder or 1 vegan bouillon
a sprinkle of seafood spice seasoning (make sure it's vegan) (optional)
few pinches of sea salt
 cup textured vegetable protein/soy protein (optional)
1-2 pieces dried beancurd sheets, reconstituted in hot water then cut into chunks (optional)
1 piece dried tremella, reconstituted in hot water then cut into chunks (optional)
1 tablespoon seaweed (optional)
1-2 pieces fried beancurd sheets (optional)

chapters.title: 3/4 cup textured vegetable protein or TVP
